The greatest power in life is knowing who you are and where you come from! We come from a lineage of Kings and Queens! @soupandchampagne is a celebration of Freedom! Haitians of African lineage coming together and creating the 1st Black Free Republic! January 1st 1804! We celebrate our revolution! The day it was decreed that Soup Joumou was no longer just for the slave owners! It was for everyone! Haiti’s 1st Supper! Let’s celebrate this day! 

This painting was a dream! We worked with @akomicsart on bringing this vision to life! You will be able to see this painting and works of other Haitian artist at Soup &
Champagne! We can’t wait to see you soon! Get your tickets now!

Limited prints will be available this week. You will be able to purchase at www.soupandchampagne.com

The biggest Haitian music award ceremony in Diaspora that creates a platform to promote the diversity of Haitian music by bringing top Haitian talents across the world on the same stage to celebrate Haitian music. Get your tickets now before it's too late.

The event featured stellar performances by Charlin Bato, Andy Beatz, T-Vice, Team Lobey, Dj Tony Mix, Fridayy, and Joe Dwet File, each adding their unique flair to the festivities.
